BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Outlander in Concert
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261018T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261018T174500
DTSTAMP:20260721T085036Z
UID:occ-1715@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Instrumental Concert
DESCRIPTION:Bear McCreary's Outlander score played by a live orchestra\, w
 ith the series' key scenes on a cinema-sized screen.\n\nThe officially lic
 ensed Outlander concert\, created with showrunner Matthew B. Roberts and t
 he show's Emmy-winning composer Bear McCreary as the series heads toward i
 ts 2026 conclusion. A live orchestra performs McCreary's score while the s
 how's most stirring moments play on a cinema-sized screen\, tracing Claire
  and Jamie's story from the standing stones of Craigh na Dun onward. The t
 ouring production premiered in Scotland and is licensed by Sony Pictures T
 elevision in collaboration with Starz. Recommended for ages 12 and up with
  parental guidance.
GEO:33.7726136;-84.3853395
LAST-MODIFIED:20260721T084853Z
LOCATION:Fox Theatre\, 660 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://foxtheatre.evenue.net/cgi-bin/ncommerce3/SEGetEventList?groupC
 ode=OUT&linkID=fta&shopperContext=&caller=&appCode
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Sonic Live In Concert
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261024T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261024T211500
DTSTAMP:20260721T085036Z
UID:occ-1716@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Instrumental Concert
DESCRIPTION:Sonic the Hedgehog's game music played live — rock band\, en
 semble\, and vocalists synced to footage from 35 years of games.\n\nA conc
 ert built from three and a half decades of Sonic the Hedgehog music\, from
  the Genesis-era chiptunes of Green Hill Zone to "Undefeatable\," performe
 d live by an ensemble with rock musicians\, electronics\, and vocalists wh
 ile moments from the games play onscreen. The program draws heavily on the
  work of Jun Senoue and Tomoya Ohtani\, the composers who shaped Sonic's s
 ound across generations. The arrangements hide musical Easter eggs for lon
 gtime fans to catch mid-show.
GEO:33.7726136;-84.3853395
LAST-MODIFIED:20260721T084853Z
LOCATION:Fox Theatre\, 660 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://foxtheatre.evenue.net/cgi-bin/ncommerce3/SEGetEventList?groupC
 ode=SON&linkID=fta&shopperContext=&caller=&appCode=
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:NieR: Orchestra Concert 12026 [YoRHa]!
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261107T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261107T214500
DTSTAMP:20260721T085036Z
UID:occ-497@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:2
CATEGORIES:Instrumental Concert
DESCRIPTION:Music from Square Enix's NieR games — full orchestra\, choru
 s\, original vocalists\, and a new narrated Automata prequel story.\n\nThe
  music of the NieR video games performed live\, presented by AWR Music Pro
 ductions and Square Enix. Eric Roth conducts a full orchestra and chorus\,
  joined by J'Nique Nicole and Emi Evans\, the singers whose voices defined
  the original game recordings. Between the music\, recorded narration from
  NieR:Automata's Japanese voice cast — including Yui Ishikawa as 2B — 
 tells the story of the Pearl Harbor Descent Operation\, the prequel to Aut
 omata\, with visuals on a giant screen. A follow-up from the team behind t
 he earlier NieR:Orchestra Concert [the end of data] tour.
GEO:33.7726136;-84.3853395
LAST-MODIFIED:20260721T084853Z
LOCATION:Fox Theatre\, 660 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://foxtheatre.evenue.net/cgi-bin/ncommerce3/SEGetEventList?groupC
 ode=NIE&linkID=fta&shopperContext=&caller=&appCode
END:VEVENT
